 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-20k","title":"Add terminal hyperlinks (OSC 8) for clickable URLs","description":"## Overview
Add OSC 8 terminal hyperlink support to make URLs clickable in supported terminals (iTerm2, Hyper, Windows Terminal, Konsole, GNOME Terminal 3.26+, etc.). This enables users to click on documentation links, file paths, and error references directly from CLI output.

## Dependencies
- **BLOCKED BY**: remote_compilation_helper-u0v (UI output abstraction layer)

## Requirements

### OSC 8 Escape Sequence Format
```
ESC ] 8 ; params ; URI ST text ESC ] 8 ; ; ST
```
Where:
- `ESC ]` = `\x1b]` (OSC introducer)
- `ST` = `\x1b\\` or `\x07` (string terminator)
- `params` = optional key=value pairs like `id=foo` (for multi-line links)
- `URI` = the clickable URL
- `text` = the displayed text

### Rust Implementation
```rust
// rch/src/ui/hyperlink.rs

/// Creates a terminal hyperlink (OSC 8) if supported
pub fn hyperlink(url: &str, text: &str, ctx: &OutputContext) -> String {
    if !ctx.supports_hyperlinks() {
        return text.to_string();
    }
    format!("\x1b]8;;{}\x1b\\{}\x1b]8;;\x1b\\", url, text)
}

/// Detects hyperlink support based on terminal capabilities
pub fn detect_hyperlink_support() -> bool {
    // Check terminal emulator
    if let Ok(term_program) = std::env::var("TERM_PROGRAM") {
        match term_program.as_str() {
            "iTerm.app" | "Hyper" | "WezTerm" | "vscode" => return true,
            _ => {}
        }
    }

    // Check TERM_FEATURES for hyperlinks
    if let Ok(features) = std::env::var("TERM_FEATURES") {
        if features.contains("hyperlinks") {
            return true;
        }
    }

    // Check VTE_VERSION for GNOME Terminal 3.26+
    if let Ok(vte) = std::env::var("VTE_VERSION") {
        if let Ok(v) = vte.parse::<u32>() {
            if v >= 5000 { // VTE 0.50+ supports hyperlinks
                return true;
            }
        }
    }

    // Windows Terminal
    if std::env::var("WT_SESSION").is_ok() {
        return true;
    }

    // Konsole 18.07+
    if std::env::var("KONSOLE_VERSION").is_ok() {
        return true;
    }

    false
}
```

### Usage Examples

#### Error Messages with Documentation Links
```rust
ctx.error(&format!(
    "Configuration file not found. {}",
    hyperlink(
        "https://rch.dev/docs/config",
        "See documentation",
        ctx
    )
));
// Output: Configuration file not found. See documentation
//         (where "See documentation" is clickable)
```

#### File Paths
```rust
let path = "~/.config/rch/workers.toml";
let full_path = expand_path(path);
let link = hyperlink(
    &format!("file://{}", full_path),
    path,
    ctx
);
ctx.info(&format!("Configuration loaded from {}", link));
```

#### Worker Hostnames
```rust
// Link to SSH connection
let link = hyperlink(
    &format!("ssh://{}@{}", worker.user, worker.host),
    &worker.id,
    ctx
);
ctx.success(&format!("Connected to {}", link));
```

### Integration Points

| Command | Link Type | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| `rch doctor` | Documentation links | "Run rch hook install" links to docs |
| `rch status` | Config file paths | Clickable path to config files |
| `rch workers list` | SSH URLs | Worker names link to SSH |
| Error messages | Help pages | "See: https://rch.dev/errors/E001" |
| `rch config validate` | Line numbers in files | file://path.toml#line=5 (if supported) |

### Fallback Behavior
When hyperlinks are NOT supported:
- Display text only (no URL)
- Optionally append URL in parentheses for important links:
  ```
  See documentation (https://rch.dev/docs/config)
  ```

